FBIS4-12905 "drnes072yy_94001" FBIS-NES-94-072 Daily Report 13 Apr 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Arab-Israeli Talks Syrian Spokesman Rejects Rabin's Format Proposals Syrian Spokesman Rejects Rabin's Format Proposals TA1304071294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0600 GMT 13 Apr 94 TA1304071294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el Hebrew BFN [Text] Syria has rejected Prime Minister Rabin's proposals to change the format of the Syrian-Israeli negotiations. An official Syrian spokesman has said that secret talks and separate agreements will weaken the Arabs and allow Israel to force its terms on them. The Syrian spokesman further said that the agreement Israel signed with the PLO did not lead to peace. Rather, it complicated the situation and increased the agony of the Arabs in the territories.
